'''Viasat Sport East''' is a television channel available in Russia, the CIS countries and the Baltic states. The channel heavily features American sports such as the [[National Hockey League]] and [[Major League Baseball]].
The channel launched in [[Russia]], [[Belarus]], [[Moldova]], [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]], [[Kazakhstan]] and the [[Baltic states]] in November 2006 in cooperation with [[ESPN America]]. It was the eighth channel launched by Viasat in Eastern Europe.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://mtg.se/en/Media/Press-releases/MTG-AND-NASN-TO-LAUNCH-NEW-SPORTS-CHANNEL-IN-EASTERN-EUROPE/|title=MTG AND NASN TO LAUNCH NEW SPORTS CHANNEL IN EASTERN EUROPE|publisher=Modern Times Group|date=October 17, 2006}}</ref> It later became available in [[Ukraine]], [[Armenia]], [[Kyrgyzstan]] and [[Uzbekistan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtg.se/en/Brands/Pay-TV/Viasat-Sport/|title=Viasat Sport East|publisher=Modern Times Group}}</ref>
In January 2010, the channel was removed from Viasat's Baltic platform, where it was replaced by [[Viasat Hockey]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.broadbandtvnews.com/2010/01/18/viasat-baltic-debuts-in-baltics/|title=Viasat Hockey debuts in Baltics|date=January 18, 2010|publisher=Broadband TV News}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.worldscreen.com/articles/display/23927|title=Viasat Hockey Headed to the Baltics|date=January 18, 2010|publisher=WorldScreen.com}}</ref> [[File:Viasat Sport old logo.png|thumb|left|200px|First Viasat Sport logo used 2006-2009]]
